<sect2><title>segv</title>
<para>
<command>segv</command> is a segmentation violation error handler, which is useful for development debugging. It is not envisaged that users of <command>GDMS</command> will need to install this. <command>segv</command> uses ld.so preload operations to catch segmentation violations, and display a backtrace...
</para>

<sect3><title>Authors</title>
<para>
Dr Andrew Tridgell wrote <command>segv</command>. It can be downloaded from his website at http://junkcode.samba.org.
</para>
</sect3>
</sect2>